    <stitle>International&#174; MaxxForce&#8482; 7 Engine Service Manual - Flywheel and Flywheel Housing - Installation
        - Crankshaft Flange
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc id="s12.4.2" svcproctype="install" graphiccount="4">
        <title>Crankshaft Flange</title>
        <figure id="f3450012029" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figM10/M10118.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="192px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Crankshaft flange</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">M12 x 68 bolt (6)</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Crankshaft flange</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <specpara>
            <caution>
                <para>To prevent engine damage, the crankshaft flange must be properly timed to maintain correct engine
                    balance.
                </para>
            </caution>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Rotate crankshaft until cylinder number 1 is at Top Dead Center (TDC).</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Inspect the crankshaft gear and crankshaft flange mating surfaces. Make sure they are free
                of debris, nicks, and dirt.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install two guide pins (made locally) into crankshaft gear bolt holes.</para>
        </step1>
        <specpara>
            <warning>
                <para>To prevent serious personal injury or death, wear heat protective gloves when installing hot
                    crankshaft flange.
                </para>
            </warning>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Heat crankshaft flange to 177&#176; C (350&#176; F).</para>
        </step1>
        <specpara>
            <caution>
                <para>To prevent engine damage, do not mar sealing surface of crankshaft flange.</para>
            </caution>
            <note>
                <para>Make sure dowel pin is installed correctly in crankshaft flange.</para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install crankshaft flange over guide pins and onto crankshaft, with dowel pin pointing at 12
                o'clock position.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove guide pins and install six old M12 x 68 bolts. Tighten bolts alternately to seat
                crankshaft flange.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Check face runout of crankshaft flange, using
                <hotlnk document="eges3451_268.xml" xrefid="s12.t3">dial indicator with magnetic base</hotlnk>
                <xref refid="s12.t3"/>. If face runout exceeds
                <hotlnk document="eges3451_266.xml" xrefid="s12.t1">specification</hotlnk>
                <xref refid="s12.t1"/>, replace crankshaft flange.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f3450012030" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figM10/M10127.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="232px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Crankshaft flange torque sequence</caption>
        </figure>
        <specpara>
            <caution>
                <para>To prevent engine damage, always install new crankshaft flange mounting bolts.</para>
            </caution>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove and discard six old bolts and loosely install six new M12 x 68 bolts. Tighten bolts
                as follows using above sequence:
            </para>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Tighten bolts to 41 N&#183;m (30 lbf&#183;ft)</para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Rotate bolts 90 degrees using above sequence.</para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Rotate bolts an additional 90 degrees using above sequence.</para>
            </step2>
        </step1>
        <specpara>
            <caution>
                <para>To prevent engine damage, install gear with circular witness groove facing out.</para>
            </caution>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install power steering idler gear assembly on power steering idler shaft.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Verify correct gear orientation and gear tooth engagement.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f3450012031" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figM10/M10117.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="192px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Power steering idler gear assembly</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">External retaining ring</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Power steering idler gear assembly</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <specpara>
            <warning>
                <para>To prevent personal injury or death, wear safety glasses with side shields when doing the
                    following procedure.
                </para>
            </warning>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install external retaining ring onto power steering idler shaft for power steering idler
                gear assembly.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Perform
                <hotlnk document="eges3451_253.xml" xrefid="s12.2.2.5.ref1">power steering idler gear assembly backlash
                    test
                </hotlnk>
                <xref refid="s12.2.2.5.ref1"/>.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install new rear seal carrier gasket on crankshaft rear oil seal carrier.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f3450012032" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figM10/M10116.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="192px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Crankshaft rear oil seal carrier</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">M8 x 25 bolt (7)</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Crankshaft rear oil seal carrier</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">M8 x 55 bolt (2)</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install crankshaft rear oil seal carrier on crankcase rear cover.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install two M8&#160;x&#160;55 bolts in lower holes of crankshaft rear oil seal carrier.
                Tighten bolts to
                <hotlnk document="eges3451_267.xml" xrefid="s12.t2">special torque</hotlnk>
                <xref refid="s12.t2"/>.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install seven M8&#160;x&#160;25 bolts in crankshaft rear oil seal carrier. Tighten bolts to
                <hotlnk document="eges3451_267.xml" xrefid="s12.t2">special torque</hotlnk>
                <xref refid="s12.t2"/>.
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
